sentences: Leeds "Lee" Collins (October 17, 1901 – July 3, 1960) was an American jazz trumpeter.
In the 1910s, he played in New Orleans alongside Louis Armstrong, Papa Celestin, and Zutty Singleton.
He moved to Chicago, Illinois, in 1924, where he replaced Louis Armstrong in King Oliver's band.
